Turmeric-Ginger-Lemon Energy Elixir (7-Day Batch)
Makes: ~500ml (lasts 5 days in fridge)
Daily Dose: 2 oz (60ml) per morning (shot glass or small cup)

Ingredients:
3-inch fresh ginger (peeled, sliced)

2-inch fresh turmeric (peeled, sliced, or 1 tsp powder)

Juice of 2 lemons (~1/4 cup / 60ml)

1/4 tsp black pepper (must for absorption)

2 cups (500ml) filtered water (hot, not boiling)

Optional: 1 tbsp honey or maple syrup (for sweetness)

Instructions:
Simmer ginger + turmeric in 2 cups hot water for 10 mins (low heat).

Strain into a glass bottle, discard solids.

Add lemon juice, black pepper, and sweetener (if using). Shake well.

Store in fridge (up to 5 days).

How to Use:
Each morning: Shake bottle, pour 2 oz (60ml), drink 15 mins before breakfast.

Optional: Dilute with warm water if too strong.